Description: A sealing from a document, much damaged, burnt and largely illegible, but probably a male head to right. The reverse is very rough. Dark-brown Nile silt.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Fund. Tanis Find 35, the House of Ashaikhet (originally read as Bakakhuiu; see Petrie 1885: 41-6, Favard-Meeks 1998: 126-32). This house is on the eastern side of the mound, east of the Great Temple, and probably outside the great enclosure wall shown in Petrie 1885: pl. [xvii]. The house contained Ptolemaic coins and probably burned down in the latter half of the second century AD. See also registration no. 1885,0101.35. Ptolemaic or Roman. Bibliog: Favard-Meeks in Brissaud and Zivie-Coche: Tanis 1987-1997 (1998) p.127.
